SIMPLE: benzene
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Benzene
<hw>Ben"zene</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Benzoin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A volatile, very
inflammable liquid, <chform>C6H6</chform>, contained in the naphtha
produced by the destructive distillation of coal, from which it is
separated by fractional distillation. The name is sometimes applied also
to the impure commercial product or <xex>benzole</xex>, and also, but
rarely, to a similar mixed product of petroleum.</def><-- called also
benzol -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Benzene nucleus</b></col>, <col><b>Benzene
ring</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a closed chain or ring,
consisting of six carbon atoms, each with one hydrogen atom attached,
regarded as the type from which the aromatic compounds are derived. This
ring formula is provisionally accepted as representing the probable
constitution of the benzene molecule, <chform>C6H6</chform>, and as the
type on which its derivatives are formed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>benzenoid</ent>⟦br⟧
